This paper is about using machine learning techniques for network intrusion detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on using the KDD dataset for testing and evaluating different classifiers, which involves data preprocessing and feature selection, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the speed of the IDS, which could potentially involve using neural networks or other optimization techniques (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves classification algorithms such as J48, MLP, and Bayes Network, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves evaluating the performance of different classifiers, which could involve software engineering principles such as testing and evaluation (cs.SE).
